The paper discusses traffic engineering and security in communication networks, which falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes protection schemes against attacks and failures, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of redundancy to improve network reliability, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of cloud networks, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed scheme to optical and IP networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
